:.START

American Airlines go expand transatlantic service 30% starting next year with six new daily flights between U.S. and Europe agriment yesterday.

American, one unit of AMR Corp. Na di nation biggest airline now.

Di new non stop flights wey start for di next May, na Chicago Warsaw, Chicago Metropolis, Miami Madrid, Dallas Barcelona, a second daily Chicago Parais, and second Sunday, Chicago Manchester flight.

Na Mikago bi di town wey big pass for Poland wey dey outside Poland.

With di new service, America go dey fly 161 flights a week to 17 European cities.

Di addition make America stand third for U.S. transatlantic carrier, behind Pan Am Corp. Pan American World Airways and Trans World Airlines.

